ing code, not in file I/O. LLM-DEP: None. COMMIT-TO-REASONING: Evidence points to Unit. No override. REJECTION-GATE: Integration was considered but rejected because the failure is in how the loader processes the YAML parser's exception, which is observable without wiring in real file readers.","test_description":"Provide the loader (or the YAML-parsing layer directly) with an in-memory string containing a deliberate YAML syntax error at a known line (e.g., a bad indentation on line 3). Assert the resulting exception or printed error contains the exact line number `3`. Test with errors at multiple line positions to confirm the line number tracks correctly rather than being hardcoded.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.62,"Integration":0.3,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Missing config directory is created and defaults file is written on first run","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure involves actual filesystem side effects — `os.makedirs` must be called correctly and the defaults file must be written with the right content to the right path. While mock-patching `os.makedirs` and `open` would verify the calls are made, it would not catch bugs like wrong permissions flags, incorrect directory nesting, or file content that fails to serialize. Wiring the loader to a real temp directory (pytest `tmp_path`) provides end-to-end coverage of directory creation + file write in a single in-process operation. REAL-INFRA: Real local filesystem via `tmp_path` — no subprocess, no network. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) Requires real filesystem I/O but no subprocess or network; tmp_path satisfies this within Integration. (b) No LLM. (c) No multi-step. Integration confirmed. COMMIT-TO-REASONING: Evidence points to Integration (real filesystem side effects, two coupled operations: mkdir + write). No override. REJECTION-GATE: System was considered but rejected — the behavior requires no subprocess invocation or external service; real filesystem access via tmp_path is local and in-process.","test_description":"Point the loader at a non-existent directory under `tmp_path` (e.g., `tmp_path / 'tool_config'`). Run the loader startup logic. Assert (1) the directory now exists on disk, (2) a defaults file (e.g., `config.yaml`) exists inside it, and (3) the file contains parseable YAML with the expected default keys. Also assert the loader continues to operate normally after writing the defaults rather than exiting with an error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.28,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10152,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":10152},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aadb911f-3b93-49d8-af82-72c8a8d3c1f3","uuid":"87d83707-01f8-41a2-a073-a4f832da558b"}
